The agent A provided the following violation scenario:The statement 'dir = stack[sp-1].dir;' assigns a new value to the function parameter 'dir' (declared as 'const lfs_mdir_t *dir'). MISRA C 2023 Rule 17.8 forbids modifying function parameters; although the pointee may be modified, the pointer parameter itself must not be changed. Reassigning 'dir' therefore violates Rule 17.8. (A compliant alternative is to copy the parameter to a local pointer variable and modify that local variable instead.)
